# PR Watch Commands

When the user types any of the commands below, **immediately run the pr-watch skill** — no clarifying questions, no preamble, just execute.

## Command Map

| Command | What to run |
|---------|-------------|
| `pr <team>` | Quick mode PR health for `<team>` (e.g. `pr gen-ai`) |
| `pr ci <team>` | CI mode PR health for `<team>` — fetch CI status for stuck PRs |
| `pr all` | Quick mode for `all-areas` team |
| `pr ci all` | CI mode for `all-areas` team |
| `pr blocked <team>` | Show only blocked PRs for `<team>` |
| `pr stale <team>` | Show only PRs waiting 2+ days for `<team>` |
| `pr bots <team>` | Show only bot PRs needing `/ok-to-test` for `<team>` |

## Rules

- `pr <team>` → **Quick mode** (no CI calls, label signals only, fast)
- `pr ci <team>` → **CI mode** (fetch `get_pull_request_status` for stuck PRs only)
- Team names come from `.cursor/skills/pr-standup/config.yaml`
- If `<team>` is not in config.yaml, use it as a raw label (e.g. `pr area/nim`)
- Never ask for confirmation — run immediately
